❌ Critical / High Priority
1) Unauthenticated fallback still exists in “normal” operation
File: engramia/api/auth.py
Lines: 82-85, 223-232

Why it matters
If ENGRAMIA_API_KEYS is empty and DB auth is not used, the API allows requests through. Yes, it logs a warning. No, that is not enough for production.

Fix

Make this behavior available only when:
ENGRAMIA_AUTH_MODE=dev
and ENGRAMIA_ALLOW_NO_AUTH=true
Otherwise fail startup or return 503 on every request.
2) ROI event collection can silently lose data under concurrency
File: engramia/analytics/collector.py
Lines: 131-135
raw = self._load_raw()
raw.append(event.model_dump())
raw = raw[-_MAX_EVENTS:]
self._storage.save(_EVENTS_KEY, raw)

Why it matters
Two concurrent writes can both read the same prior list and overwrite each other.

Fix

JSON backend: lock around append
Postgres backend: append rows transactionally, don’t emulate append with JSON list overwrite
3) Async “jobs” are not truly production-durable
Files: engramia/api/routes.py, engramia/jobs/service.py
Relevant lines: routes.py:73-92

Why it matters
Prefer: respond-async gives the shape of async, but not necessarily the guarantees users will assume (durability, retries, backpressure, persistence, crash recovery).

Fix

If this is a product promise, use a real job queue
If not, label it clearly as “best-effort background execution”
